cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning techniques for text classification. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of large pre-trained language models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of attention-based Transformer networks, which is a popular architecture for NLP tasks and falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of real-world datasets and applications, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
